info.body: above是常考单词,所以学生一定要知道 above,over 和on在表示位置时 的用法区别:

items.content:
指笼统的上方,表示位置之高;反义词为below。
The water came above our knees. 水没过了我们的膝盖。

指垂直的上方,比较精确,反义词为under。
The light is over my head. 灯在我头顶上方。

指“在...上面”,两者有表面接触,表示一件东西在另一件之上。
There is a book on the desk. 桌子上有一本书

items.content: 是形容词...多指人(寂寞的)...多指地方(荒凉的)。

examples.en: I've already had two cups of coffee, but I can still have another.

info.body: another是常考单词...比较与the other 的用法区别:

items.content: 是指三个及三个以上的另一个
items.ex: I don't like this one, show me another.

items.content: 是指两个当中的另一个
items.ex: I have two hands. One is the right hand and the other is left. [cite: 497-502]

examples.en: The maths teacher wonders if anyone knows the answer to the question.
examples.cn: 数学老师想知道是否有人知道这个问题的答案。

examples.en: She didn't answer my letter.
examples.cn: 她没有给我回信。

examples.en: Last night I didn't answer your phone because I was seeing the film Dune.
examples.cn: 昨晚我没有接听你的电话,因为我正在看电影《沙丘》。

translations.translation: (用于疑问句、否定句、条件句)一些,什么;任何的,任一的

examples.en: We shouldn't make friends with any dishonest persons.
examples.cn: 我们不应该和任何不诚实的人交朋友。

examples.en: Tom's Chinese is better than any other boy's in the class.
examples.cn: 汤姆的中文比班上其他男孩都好。

examples.en: I asked my friend for some ink, but she didn't have any.
examples.cn: 我问我的朋友要一些墨水,但是她也没有。

info.body: any是常考单词...比较与some的用法区别:

items.content: 用于肯定句中; 表示建议、请求...多用some
items.ex: Would you like some coffee?

items.content: 用于否定句或疑问句中; 表示“任何”...起强调作用时,它可以用于肯定句中
items.ex: Any student can answer this question.

items.content: not... any longer与not... any more (再也不...)意思相同
items.ex: I can't wait any longer/any more. [cite: 524-533]

examples.en: There isn't anyone/anybody in the classroom.
examples.cn: 教室里没有任何人。

translations.translation: 什么事(物);任何事(物);任何东西

examples.en: Alice didn't say anything at the meeting last week, did she?
examples.cn: 在上周的会议上爱丽丝没有说什么,是吗?

examples.en: We will go anywhere you like.
examples.cn: 我们会去你喜欢的任何地方。

examples.en: I apologized to the girl for my being late.
examples.cn: 我因为迟到而向那位女孩道歉。

info.body: apologize to sb.与say sorry to sb.意思相同,在句中可以互换。

items.content: The boy apologized to his friend... = The boy said sorry to his friend...
items.ex: 这个男孩对他的朋友说“对不起”,因为他打碎了他的杯子。 [cite: 547-550]

examples.en: As soon as the boss appeared, the noisy office became quiet.
examples.cn: 老板一出现,喧闹的办公室马上安静了下来。

examples.cn: 因为我非常熟悉这一地区,他们希望我领他们参观一下。

examples.cn: 当孩子们在游乐园里看到这么多具有吸引力的卡通人物时,他们很激动。

examples.cn: 他有许多典型澳大利亚人的习惯。

examples.cn: 他虽然中等个头,但球打得比队里任何一个人都好。

examples.cn: 我认为他会成为一名宇航员。

examples.cn: 祝贺你!你有机会成为一名交换学生。

examples.cn: 今天的天气多么晴朗啊!我们去海滩野餐好吗?

examples.en: Beat the mixture until it was smooth and creamy.
examples.cn: 搅拌混合物直至丝滑的奶油状。

info.body:
beat 是常考单词,学生一定要掌握其用法,及比较与hit的用法区别:
beat 表示接连地‘打;敲’。
例如:beat sb. senseless 把某人打得失去知觉
The rain was beating against the window. 雨打在窗户上。
hit 表示用力地‘打(一下);击中’。
例如:I hit him a hard blow. 我重重给了他一拳。
He fired and hit the target. 他开枪射中了靶子。

examples.en: Bali is a beautiful place. It attracts a lot of tourists every year.

examples.cn: 这首轻音乐很动听。我非常喜欢。

examples.en: She sang beautifully when she was watching TV.
examples.cn: 她在看电视的时候优美地唱起了歌。

examples.en: He was beginning to enjoy the beauties of nature.
examples.cn: 他要开始享受大自然之美。

examples.cn: 请长话短说,因为我有急事。

examples.en: The man is called 'Wolf Dad' because of his cruel way of parenting.
examples.cn: 那个人被称作“狼爸”是因为他残酷的养育方式。

info.body:
because 是常考单词,所以学生一定要掌握其用法:
because 后面跟句子;because of 后面跟名词。
例如:The cars moved slowly because it snowed heavily.
= The cars moved slowly because of the heavy snow.
因为下大雪,汽车行驶得很慢。

info.body:
become是常考单词,所以学生一定要掌握其用法: become 后面跟形容词。
例如:He became very excited. 他变得很激动。

examples.cn: 尽管彼得才5岁,他正在学习自己整理床铺。

examples.cn: 弗兰克和玛丽一早就打开卧室的电脑,因为他们想得到最新消息。

examples.cn: 我数学不如他。

examples.cn: 这辆汽车突然刹停,后面那辆公共汽车差点儿撞到它。

examples.cn: 人不吃东西能活多久?

expand: believable adj. 可信的;可靠的
believably adv. 可信地;可靠地
belief n. 信仰;信心;信念;相信

examples.en: There is a bell on the wall.
examples.cn: 墙上有个钟。

examples.cn: 这幢房子是属于温特先生的吗?

examples.en: Please do not write below this line.

info.body:
below是常考单词,学生一定要厘清 below 和 under 这两个词语的意思及用法:
below 表示‘在...下面’,但不一定是指在某物的正下方,而是指低于某物,其反义词是 above; under 表示‘在...下方’,是指在某物的正下方,其反义词是 over。
例如:The noise came from below the floor. 声音来自地板下面。
Shall I write my name on, above or below the line? 我该把名字签在横线线上、横线上方还是横线下方?

info.body:
borrow 是常考单词,学生一定要掌握其意思,及比较与lend, keep的用法区别:
borrow 是向别人借用不属于自己的东西,表示‘借进’,其结构是:borrow sb. sth. = borrow sth. from/of sb.,但不能与表示一段时间的状语连用。
lend是将自己的东西借给别人使用,表示‘借出’,其结构是:lend sb. sth. = lend sth. to sb.,但不能与表示一段时间的状语连用。
keep 是表示‘持有(某物);保持(某种状态)’,可以与表示一段时间的状语连用。

info.body:
bring, take, fetch, carry 这四个词语的意思较相近,都有‘拿’的意思,比较他们的用法区别:
bring 表示‘带来’,就是从其他地方将东西拿到或带到说话人处。
take 表示‘拿走’,就是从说话人处将东西拿走或带走。
fetch 表示‘(去)拿来;(去)请来’,就是从说话人处出发到其他地方将某物拿到或请某人来到说话人处。
carry 表示‘携带;运送;搬运’,不一定将某物拿到或某人带到说话人处,可以从任何地方到任何地方。

info.body:
buy是常考时态的瞬间动词,所以学生一定要知道瞬间动词不能和 for 加一段时间构成完成时态。瞬间动词与状态性动词的转换如下:
The film began ten minutes ago. → The film has been on for ten minutes.
He joined the army two years ago. → He has been in/served in the army for two years.
She became a teacher three years ago. → She has been a/worked as a teacher for three years.
He borrowed a book a week ago. → He has kept the book for a week.
He died two days ago. → He has been dead for two days.
He bought a book the day before yesterday. → He has had the book for two days.
He left Shanghai last year. → He has been away from Shanghai for a year.

expand: clearly adv. 清晰地;明亮地;清楚地

info.body:
clear 是常考单词,与clean一样,既可作动词,又可作形容词。比较其用法区别:
clear作动词时,意为‘扫清’,表示将多余的、不需要的东西拿走或清除;作形容词时,意为‘清晰的、明亮的’。
clean作动词时,意为‘打扫干净’,表示可以用水将某物洗干净;作形容词时,意为‘清洁的、干净的’。

info.body:
clothes是常考单词,学生一定要掌握其用法,及比较与cloth, clothing 的用法区别:
clothes 是复数名词,表示衣服,前面不能用数量词和不定冠词,但可以用 some, these, those, many, (a) few, a suit of 等词语来修饰。
cloth 是不可数名词,表示衣料,布匹,前面只能用 a piece of, three yards of 等词语来修饰。
clothing 是不可数名词,表示衣服,前面可以用 winter, articles of 等词语来修饰。常与动词 buy, donate, provide 等搭配。

info.body: either是常考单词，常出现在主谓一致的练习中，所以学生一定要知道： either...or...,neither..nor...,not only..but also...,there be等词语在连接多个主语  时，谓语动词用单数还是复数形式取决于离它最近的那个主语。

items.ex: Either you or he is going.要么你去，要么他去。
Neither I nor you are wrong.我和你都没有错。
Not only you but also I was surprised by the news. 不仅你，连我也对这条消息感到惊讶。

info.body:
enjoy是常考单词,其后面一定要跟动名词。同时要牢记以下这些动词和动词词组,其后面也一定要跟动名词:
enjoy, deny, finish, keep, practise, mind, prefer, spend, be busy, be worth, be good at, be/get used to, feel like, give up, do well in, pay attention to, what about, how about, look forward to, keep/stop/prevent sb. from

translations.translation: 使人愉快的;使人欢乐的

examples.en: We hope you had an enjoyable holiday.
examples.cn: 我们希望您度过一个愉快的假期。

examples.cn: 我相当喜欢这首音乐。它使人愉悦。

examples.cn: 两条牛仔裤中,我选择了更便宜的一条,因为我带的钱不够。

examples.cn: 你知道中国船员是否已经设法摆脱了海盗?

examples.cn: 今天,他们的思想仍然影响着我们,尤其是在艺术、科学、文学和哲学方面。

examples.cn: 她甚至都没为她的错误道歉。

info.body:
even 是常考单词,所以学生一定要掌握以下这些词语的用法:
even, much, far, still, a bit, a little, a lot 等词语可以修饰比较级,如:a bit bigger, much better, far more useful, even earlier, still greater, a little longer。
例如:Don't you think traveling by train is much cheaper and far more enjoyable than a trip by air? 你不认为坐火车旅行比坐飞机旅行更便宜、更愉快吗?

examples.en: What an amazing performance the singer gave at the opening ceremony yesterday evening!

examples.en: Both my husband and I think it is the most amusing story we have ever heard.
examples.cn: 我丈夫和我都认为这是我们听到过的最有趣的故事。

examples.en: Many people are unaware of how much sugar they take in every day.
examples.cn: 很多人没有意识到他们每天摄入了多少糖。

examples.en: If everyone takes a bus instead of driving a car, there will be less air pollution.
examples.cn: 如果每个人都坐公共汽车而不是驾驶汽车,空气污染将会减少。

examples.en: Please speak louder, so that everybody in the hall can hear you clearly.

info.body:
谚语 If everyone gives a love to each other, the world will become much more beautiful.
如果人人都献出一点爱,世界将会更美好。

examples.en: These are my everyday shoes, not my best ones.
examples.cn: 这些是我平常穿的鞋,不是最好的鞋。

info.body:
everyday是常考单词,学生一定要掌握 everyday 和 every day的用法区别:
everyday 是形容词,意思是“每天的,日常的”。
every day 是表示时间的短语,作状语,意思是“每天”。
例如:Computers are part of everyday life. 电脑是日常生活的一部分。
Such things do not happen every day. 这种事情不是每天都会发生的。
You can improve your English by reading English newspapers every day.
通过每天阅读英文报纸,你可以提高英语水平。

examples.en: Kevin is so independent that he always tries to do everything by himself.
examples.cn: 凯文是如此独立,以至于他总是设法自己去做每一件事。

examples.en: Where have you been? I looked everywhere for you.
examples.cn: 你去哪儿了?我到处找你。

examples.cn: 那你究竟在忙什么?

expand: exact adj. 确切的;精确的

examples.en: After we pass the exams, we will celebrate by having a party next week.

expand: examine v. 检查,细查;对...进行考试

examples.en: The officers at the airport examine every traveler's passport carefully.
examples.cn: 机场工作人员仔细检查每一个旅客的护照。

examples.en: I don't quite understand what you said. Would you please give us another example?
examples.cn: 我不明白你说什么。请给我们另外举一个例子好吗?

examples.en: An excellent story is the key to making a successful film.
examples.cn: 一个优秀的故事是拍一部成功电影的关键。

examples.en: I think no one can help me except you.
examples.cn: 我想除了你之外没有人能帮助我。

examples.en: Everyone in our class has brought his dictionary to class except me.
examples.cn: 除了我以外,我们班上每个人都带了词典到教室。

info.body:
except 是常考单词,所以学生一定要掌握 besides, except, except for 之间的用法区别:
besides 作“除...之外”时,表示“另外附加”的含义,相当于“加法”。
except 用于表示同类事物之间的关系,其意为“除...以外”“除去”。常用在 all, whole, any, every, no, anything, anybody, anyone, everything, everybody, everyone 等词之后,相当于“减法”。
except for 不表示同类事物之间的关系,for后面的词,往往是补充说明主语的某个方面。可以理解成有点“美中不足”的意思,肯定了一个事物的大部分属性,只否定其中的一小部分。
例如:Jack also went fishing besides Tom. 除了汤姆,杰克也去钓鱼了。
We all went fishing except Tom. 除了汤姆,我们都去钓鱼了。
The article is excellent, except for a few grammar mistakes. 这篇文章很好,除了有点语法错误。(语法错误和文章不是同类事物)
Smith is a good man, except for his bad temper. 史密斯是个好人,就是脾气不好。

examples.en: The Italian exchange student was thankful to the host for his care and help.
examples.cn: 这位意大利的交换学生感谢接待方对他的关心和帮助。

examples.en: The students exchanged ideas during the group project.
examples.cn: 学生们在小组项目中交换了想法。

examples.en: Jack won the second prize in the school reading contest and he felt very excited.
examples.cn: 杰克在学校的阅读比赛中获得二等奖,他感到非常兴奋。

expand: excite v. 使激动;使兴奋
exciting adj. 令人兴奋的;令人激动的

translations.translation: 令人兴奋的;令人激动的

examples.en: How exciting it is to travel around the world by bike!
examples.cn: 骑自行车环游世界,这是多么令人兴奋啊!

info.body:
excited 和 exciting 都是与 excite 相关的形容词,但它们的含义和用法有一定区别:
excited 表示“感到兴奋的;激动的”,通常用来修饰人,或与人的感受、表情、行为等相关的名词,如voice, face等,强调人自身因为某件事或物而产生兴奋、激动的情绪;也可作表语,说明主语的状态。
例如:The excited children opened their Christmas presents. 兴奋的孩子们打开了他们的圣诞礼物。
He was excited about the upcoming trip. 他对即将到来的旅行感到兴奋。
exciting 表示“令人兴奋的;使人激动的”,主要用于修饰事物,说明该事物具有能够引起他人兴奋、激动的特性;可作定语放在名词前,或作表语说明主语的性质。
例如:The football game was really exciting. 这场足球比赛真的很令人兴奋。
It's an exciting opportunity for her. 对她来说,这是一个令人兴奋的机会。

examples.en: Excuse me, what time is it now?
examples.cn: 对不起,请问现在几点了?

examples.en: There's no excuse for behaviour like that.
examples.cn: 别为那样的行为找借口。

phrase.cn: (因打扰别人或失礼表示歉意)对不起;劳驾

examples.en: To keep fit, we should get rid of unhealthy eating habits and do more exercise.
examples.cn: 为了强身健体,我们应该摒弃不健康的饮食习惯,多做运动。

examples.en: You should exercise more.
examples.cn: 你应该多多锻炼。

info.body:
exercise是常考单词,它既是可数名词,也是不可数名词,所以学生一定要掌握其用法:
1) exercise 表示“体育锻炼,训练,运动”的时候,它是不可数名词。
例如:I walk to work every day because it is good exercise. 我每天步行上班,因为那是很好的运动。
Swimming is one of the healthiest forms of exercise. 游泳是最有益于健康的运动方式之一。
Do more exercise every day and you'll be stronger than before. 每天做更多的运动,你会比以前更强壮。
2) exercise 表示“做操”或“练习(题)”的时候,它是可数名词,要用复数形式。
例如:We won't do morning exercises if it rains tomorrow. 如果明天下雨,我们就不做早操。
We do English exercises to help us learn good English. 我们做英文练习为了学好英语。
He is doing an exercise in English grammar. 他在做英语语法练习。

examples.en: Although it was getting dark, many people were still waiting outside Shanghai Museum to visit the exhibition.
examples.cn: 虽然天渐渐黑了,上海博物馆外还有许多人等着参观展览。

examples.en: Does life exist on Mars?
examples.cn: 火星上有生命吗?

examples.cn: 顾客开始走向距离他的停车点最近的出口。

examples.en: At the end of the third scene the actress exits.
examples.cn: 这位女演员于第三场结束时退场。

examples.en: Ben and Lily have one child and they are expecting the second one in July.

info.body:
expect是常考单词,常出现在保持句意基本不变的句型转换练习中,所以学生一定要知道:expect与look forward to 意思相同,在句中可以互换。
例如:I'm expecting to receive a letter from you.
= I'm looking forward to hearing from you.
我期待收到你的来信。

examples.en: This beautiful skirt is as expensive as that red scarf. = This beautiful skirt is the same price as that red scarf.

examples.en: He had little experience in managing a team, but he learned quickly and soon became good at it.
examples.cn: 他几乎没有管理团队的经验,但学得很快,不久就驾轻就熟了。

examples.en: The experience in Australia in July was truly unforgettable.
examples.cn: 7月份在澳大利亚的经历确实难忘。

expand: experienced adj. 有经验的;熟练的;有见识的

info.body:
experience 是常考单词,所以学生一定要知道 experience作“经验”解时,是不可数的;作“经历”解时,是可数的。
例如:He has a lot of experience in the rearch. 在这项研究上他很有经验。
He has a lot of experiences of travelling. 他有很多旅游的经历。

examples.en: Now the good method is widely used in the experiments.

examples.cn: 考试一结束,我就会与家人一起去度假。

info.body:
family是常考单词,所以学生一定要正确使用这个词。
1) family 若被看作整体时,后接单数动词。
2) family 若被看作组成该集体的各个成员时,后接复数动词。
例如:The family is a very happy one. 这户人家很幸福。
The family are very pleased about the news. 全家人对此消息感到非常高兴。

examples.cn: 我们惊讶地获悉那位法国著名影星的死讯。

examples.cn: 西蒙跑得很快。约翰跑得更快。但刘翔跑得最快。

examples.en: That clock's an hour fast.
examples.cn: 那个钟快了一个小时。

examples.en: She got quickly into her car and fastened the seat-belt.
examples.cn: 她迅速钻进她的车里并系紧安全带。

info.body:
find 是常考单词,所以学生一定要掌握 find, keep, make, leave, get, set 等单词+名词+形容词,表示状态的搭配用法。
例如:find the man dead 发现那个人死了
keep the room clean 保持房间清洁
make the city greener 使城市更绿
leave the door open 让门开着
get everything ready 准备好一切
set the man free 让人自由

examples.cn: 邮递员在楼下大叫:“安德森先生,这里有你的信。”

info.body:
forget是常考单词,所以学生一定要掌握 forget doing 和 forget to do 的用法区别:
forget doing 表示忘记做过的某事(已做)。
forget to do 表示忘记去做某件事(没做)。
例如:I'll never forget meeting my school headmaster for the first time. 我永远忘不了和我小学校长初次见面的情景。
The light in the office is still on. I forgot to turn it off. 办公室的灯还亮着,我忘记关了。

examples.cn: 在极冷的天气下,我也不会感到很冷。

examples.cn: 埃菲尔铁塔是一个著名的法国地标。

examples.cn: 我们是上星期五搬进公寓的。

examples.cn: 主菜是煎牛排。

info.body: 谚语 A friend in need is a friend indeed. 患难见真情。

translations.translation: 朋友般的;友好的;友爱的

examples.en: When we were visiting the small town, the people there were very friendly to us.
examples.cn: 我们参观小镇时,那里的人们对我们很友好。

examples.cn: 我的狗很温驯,从不咬人,所以你不必害怕。

info.body:
frightened 是常考单词,学生一定要掌握其与frightening 的用法区别:
frightened 用于形容人的感受, frightening 用于形容事物。
例如:Lili is frightened of cockroaches. 莉莉很怕蟑螂。
The forest was very dark and frightening. 森林很黑暗恐怖。

examples.en: My trip to Phuket Island was really a frightening experience.
examples.cn: 我的普吉岛之旅真是一次可怕的经历。

examples.en: A soldier who doesn't want to be a general is not a good soldier.
examples.cn: 不想当将军的士兵不是好士兵。

examples.cn: 我们应该关爱年轻的一代人。

info.body: gently 是常考单词,是由形容词 gentle 转换而来。学生一定要牢记在中考考纲中有些形容词去e再加y即可转换为副词,如:possible—possibly(可能,也许), simple—simply(简单地), terrible—terribly(可怕地)。

examples.cn: 他们是德国人,所以他们会说德语。

examples.cn: 你认为德国人聪明吗?

examples.cn: 我们在德国餐厅吃午饭好吗?

examples.cn: 你知道德国的人口是多少吗?

examples.en: After taking tennis classes, Tim is getting much stronger than he was one year ago.
examples.cn: 上了网球课之后,蒂姆比一年前强壮多了。

examples.en:
She looked unhappy today. What's wrong with her?

examples.cn:
——她今天看上去不高兴。她怎么了?
——英语她得了一个“D”。

examples.en: I got to the station at half past four.
examples.cn: 我于4点半到达车站。

examples.en: It's our family tradition to exchange gifts on New Year's Eve.

examples.cn: 对于这样一个小女孩,在10分钟内就解决了这个棘手的问题,太不寻常了。

examples.cn: 离开学校时,所有的学生都感谢老师给了他们良好的教育。

examples.en: I am glad to hear from you.

examples.en: I will be glad to do it for you.

examples.en: It is said that eight glasses of water a day can help you keep fit.
examples.cn: 有人说,每天8杯水可以帮助你保持健康。

examples.en: The glasses are made of fine glass.

examples.en: Mike hurt one of his feet in an accident yesterday. Shall we go and see him after school?

examples.en: I won't go to the party unless I'm invited.

info.body:
go是常考单词,所以学生一定要掌握 have gone to, have been to, have been in 的用法区别:
have gone to 意为“到某地去”,说话时该人不在现场,一般不用第一人称和第二人称代词作句子的主语。
例如:— Where is Jim? 吉姆在哪里?
- He has gone to England. 他去英国了。(尚未回来)
Mr. Wang isn't here. He has gone to Qingdao. 王先生不在这里。他去青岛了。
have been to 意为“曾经去过某地”,现在已不在那里了。后可接表示次数的词,如 once, twice, three times等,也可和 before, just, never, ever 等词连用。
例如:My father has been to Beijing twice. 我父亲去过北京两次。
I have never been to the Great Wall. 我从未去过长城。
have been in 表示“在某地待了多少时间”,句尾常接for+时间段,或since +时间点,或句首有How long。
例如:I have been in Shanghai for three years. 我到上海已有3年了。

examples.en: Finally, Jack achieved his goal and became the owner of a company.
examples.cn: 最后,杰克实现了他的目标,成为了一家公司的老板。

examples.cn: 她把球踢进球网,为球队得了分。

examples.cn: 真金不怕火炼。

info.body: 谚语 All things in their being are good for something. 天生我材必有用。

examples.en: The government is going to widen the road this coming summer.

helpless adj. 无助的;没有帮助的

examples.cn: 但你有没有听说过森林火灾有助于森林生态的发展呢?

examples.en: The mother felt so helpless when she knew her child was seriously ill.
examples.cn: 当这位母亲得知自己的孩子病得很重时,她感到非常无助。

examples.en: I was born here. I'm quite familiar with the streets in this town.
examples.cn: 我出生在这里。我对这个小镇的街道相当熟悉。

examples.en: Though they are really great, they have never thought of themselves as heroes.
examples.cn: 虽然他们真的很伟大,但他们从来没有认为自己是英雄。

examples.en: I'm still hesitating.
examples.cn: 我仍然在犹豫。

examples.en: The boy hid in the tree.
examples.cn: 这个小男孩躲在树里。

examples.en: Nowadays the oil price in the world is getting much higher than before.
examples.cn: 如今世界上的石油价格比以前高得多。

examples.en: Shanghai Tower is one of the highest buildings in Shanghai.
examples.cn: 上海中心大厦是上海最高建筑物之一。

examples.en: I got out of breath running up the hill from the station.
examples.cn: 我从车站跑上山顶,连气都喘不上来了。

examples.en: The book is based on historical events.
examples.cn: 这本书是根据历史事件写成的。

examples.en: Southwold, a seaside town in England, has a history of more than thirteen centuries.
examples.cn: 索思沃尔德,一个英国海边的小镇,有1300多年的历史。

translations.translation: 打,撞,击中,碰撞;达到(某水平)

examples.en: You hit my head.
examples.cn: 你打了我的头。

examples.en: The company's sales hit a record high last quarter.
examples.cn: 公司上季度的销售额达到了历史新高。

examples.en: You know Mike's hobby is playing football, but mine is collecting stamps.
examples.cn: 你知道迈克的爱好是踢足球,但我的爱好是集邮。

translations.translation: 拿;抱;握住;举行;进行;保持;容纳;使...保持在某位置

examples.en: I can hold the baby.
examples.cn: 我能抱这个小孩。

examples.en: An international meeting on foreign language teaching will be held in Beijing next month.
examples.cn: 外语教学国际会议下月将在北京举行。

expand: holder n. 支托(或握持)...之物

examples.en: The hole is too small, I cannot push my arm through.
examples.cn: 这个洞太小了,我的胳膊伸不过去。

examples.en: I will fly to Qingdao for my holiday this weekend.
examples.cn: 这个周末我将飞往青岛度假。

examples.en: Frank works with others from home through computers.
examples.cn: 弗兰克在家里通过电脑与其他人联系办公。

examples.en: The earthquake in that country left thousands of people homeless.
examples.cn: 发生在那个国家的地震使成千上万的人无家可归。

examples.en: He returned to his hometown in the spring of 1917.
examples.cn: 他在1917年的春天回到了家乡。

examples.en: Don't go out of the classroom until your homework is finished.
examples.cn: 做完家庭作业前不准离开教室。

examples.en: Children are educated to be honest when they are very young.
examples.cn: 在孩子们还很小的时候,就要教育他们诚实。

expand: dishonesty n. 不诚实;不正直的行为

examples.en: Honesty is the most important thing for a person.
examples.cn: 对一个人来说,诚实是最重要的。

examples.en: I like to eat honey.
examples.cn: 我喜欢吃蜂蜜。

examples.en: It is an honour for me to be chosen as a group leader of our class project.
examples.cn: 被选为我们班级项目的组长,对我来说是一种荣誉。

examples.en: If we don't give up hope, we will surely succeed.
examples.cn: 如果我们不放弃希望,我们一定会成功的。

examples.en: I hope you will succeed.
examples.cn: 我希望你能成功。

translations.translation: 满怀希望的;抱有希望的;表现出希望的;给人以希望的

examples.en: Surgeons were hopeful of saving the sight in Sara's left eye.
examples.cn: 外科医生有望保住萨拉的左眼视力。

examples.en: My sister felt so sad to find that it was hopeless to clean her favourite T-shirt.
examples.cn: 我妹妹难过地发现,清洗干净她最喜欢的T恤衫是没指望了。

examples.en: His face is horrible.
examples.cn: 他的脸很恐怖。

examples.en: When the horse finished the race, its sides were wet all over with sweat.
examples.cn: 当这匹马跑完比赛,它浑身上下都是汗水。

examples.en: The doctors in that hospital always examine patients with great care.
examples.cn: 该院医生总是细心地为患者检查身体。

translations.translation: 主人;节目主持人(hostess n. 女主人;女节目主持人)

examples.en: I'm the host of the house.
examples.cn: 我是这间房子的主人。

examples.en: He's the host.
examples.cn: 他是主持人。

expand: hostess n. 女主人;女节目主持人

examples.en: In such hot weather, people lived comfortably with air conditioners.
examples.cn: 在如此炎热的天气里,空调使人们生活舒适。

examples.en: This curry is very hot.
examples.cn: 这咖喱特别辣。

examples.en: I like to eat hot-dog.
examples.cn: 我喜欢吃热狗。

examples.en: The Magic Hotel is amazing because it's completely underwater.
examples.cn: 魔术酒店很奇妙,因为它完全在水下。

examples.en: Thanks to Mrs. Lin! With her help, we finished our work an hour earlier.
examples.cn: 谢谢林太太!在她的帮助下,我们提前一个小时完成了工作。

examples.en: What good news it is! The government is planning to build more low-cost houses for its people.
examples.cn: 政府正计划为本国人民建造更多低价住房。真是好消息啊!

examples.en: Would you like me to help you with the housework?
examples.cn: 我帮你做家务好吗?

translations.translation: (方法、手段、状态)怎样;如何;(程度、数量、价钱)多少;(感叹)多么

examples.en: I really don't know how to answer your question.
examples.cn: 我真的不知道该如何回答你的问题。

examples.en: How about having a picnic?
examples.cn: 去野餐如何?

examples.en: However, modern technology has changed all that.
examples.cn: 然而,现代技术已经改变了所有这一切。

examples.en: However he tries, he never succeeds.
examples.cn: 无论他怎样尝试,都没能成功。

examples.en: He greeted her with a loving hug.
examples.cn: 他以一个深情的拥抱来迎接她。

translations.translation: 巨大的,庞大的;极多的;程度高的

examples.en: This is really huge amounts of money, but it is much less than we need.
examples.cn: 这实在是一笔巨款,但跟我们所需的还差得很远。

examples.en: Her greatness lies in her deep understanding of human nature.
examples.cn: 她的伟大之处在于她对人性的深刻了解。

examples.en: This new book brings together a few stories in a humorous way.
examples.cn: 这本新书以幽默的方式把一些故事串联在一起。

examples.en: The animals can go hungry because their food has been damaged in the forest fire.
examples.cn: 因为食物在这次森林火灾中遭到破坏,所以动物们可能要挨饿了。

examples.en: I've hunted everywhere but I can't find it.
examples.cn: 我到处都找遍了,就是找不到。

examples.en: When I hurried to the cinema, the film had been on for ten minutes.
examples.cn: 当我匆匆赶到电影院时,电影已经开始10分钟了。

translations.translation: 伤害(身体、感情等);痛;使受伤痛;使烦恼

examples.en: If you feel that it hurts you, it will probably hurt the rest too.
examples.cn: 如果你觉得它伤害了你,它也可能会伤害其他人。

examples.en: I love my husband.
examples.cn: 我爱我的丈夫。

examples.en: It is made of ice.
examples.cn: 它是由冰做的。

examples.en: I like to eat ice-cream.
examples.cn: 我喜欢吃冰淇淋。

examples.en: The idea to go to Shanghai Chenshan Botanical Garden sounds wonderful.
examples.cn: 去上海辰山植物园,这个主意好极了。

translations.translation: (连接状语从句)如果,假使;(连接宾语从句)是否,是不是

examples.en: I won't go to Kitty's birthday party if she doesn't invite me.
examples.cn: 如果姬蒂不邀请我,我不会去她的生日聚会。

examples.en: I don't know if he will come tomorrow, if he comes, please call me.
examples.cn: 我不知道他明天是否会来,如果他来了,请打电话给我。

examples.en: The government had ignored his views on the subject.
examples.cn: 政府忽视了他对这一问题的看法。

examples.en: John is seriously ill, so you ought to spend more time caring for him these days.
examples.cn: 约翰病得很重,所以这些天你应该多花些时间照顾他。

examples.en: Don't worry about my illness; what I need is nothing but a few days' rest.
examples.cn: 不要为我的病担心,我只要休息几天就好了。

examples.en: I can't imagine what has happened.
examples.cn: 我想象不出发生了什么事。

expand: imaginative adj. 富有想象力的;创新的

examples.en: I'll do it immediately.
examples.cn: 我马上就做。

examples.en: More and more people have realized the importance of saving water.
examples.cn: 越来越多的人已经意识到了节约水的重要性。

expand: important adj. 重要的;有重大影响的

examples.en: It's important to keep as many cultural traditions as possible.
examples.cn: 尽可能多地保留文化传统很重要。

examples.en: It's quite impossible for one with little experience to finish the task within two days.
examples.cn: 对于一个几乎没有经验的人来说,要在两天内完成这项工作是不可能的。

examples.en: Her gentleness has given me a deep impression.
examples.cn: 她的和蔼可亲给我留下了很深的印象。

expand: impress v. 给...留下深刻的好印象
impressive adj. 给人深刻印象的

examples.en: To improve our English, our teacher asks us to read English newspapers every day.
examples.cn: 为了提高我们的英语水平,老师要求我们每天阅读英文报纸。

translations.translation: 在...(位置)里(内);在...(时间);在...(情况、状态)中;以...(方法);使用...(语言);穿;戴

examples.en: She found a note in the book.
examples.cn: 她在书里发现了一张纸条。

examples.en: The Titanic struck an iceberg and sank on its first voyage in April, 1912.
examples.cn: “泰坦尼克”号在1912年4月第一次远航中撞上冰山并沉没。

examples.en: She shortened the skirt by an inch.
examples.cn: 她把裙子缩短了一英寸。

examples.en: The traditional breakfast in this area includes bread, cakes and eggs.
examples.cn: 这个地区的传统早餐包括面包、蛋糕和鸡蛋。

examples.en: I've got three days' holiday including New Year's Day.
examples.cn: 包括元旦在内,我有3天假。

examples.en: She has an annual income of ¥330,000.
examples.cn: 她年收入33万人民币。

examples.en: I'll increase your income.
examples.cn: 我将增加你的收入。

examples.en: We have seen a great increase in the use of renewable energy in the past five years.
examples.cn: 在过去5年里,我们看到可再生能源的使用量大幅增长。

examples.en: Parents should understand that they can't do everything for their children and kids have to learn to be independent.
examples.cn: 父母们应该明白,他们不能为孩子做所有事。孩子必须学会独立。

examples.en: I like indoor activities.
examples.cn: 我喜欢室内运动。

examples.en: Our industry is expanding.
examples.cn: 我们的产业正在发展壮大。

translations.translation: 影响;作用;影响力;支配力
影响;左右;对...起作用;支配

examples.en: Van Gogh had a major influence on the development of modern painting.
examples.cn: 梵高对现代绘画的发展有着重大影响。

translations.translation: 信息;消息;情报;资料;资讯

examples.en: It is impossible for us to memorise so much information by just reading once.
examples.cn: 要记住这么多的信息,只读一次对我们来说是不可能的。

examples.en: Don't write your exercise in red ink.
examples.cn: 不要用红墨水做练习。

examples.en: The mouse is inside the box.
examples.cn: 老鼠在盒子里。

examples.en: Do you mind turning on the electric fan? It is a bit hot inside.
examples.cn: 你介意打开风扇吗?里面有一点热。

examples.en: You can have pizza for dinner, or you can try the noodles instead.
examples.cn: 你晚餐可以吃比萨饼,或者可以试试面条。

examples.en: Instead of going further, the tourists took a rest in the hotel nearby.
examples.cn: 游客没有走得更远,就在附近的酒店休息了。

translations.translation: 用法说明;命令,指令;指示;指导

examples.en: Follow the safety instructions, or you could end up in a dangerous situation.
examples.cn: 遵循安全指示,否则你可能会陷入危险境地。

examples.en: In the end, he lost interest in learning Japanese.
examples.cn: 最终,他对学习日语失去了兴趣。

expand: interested adj. 感兴趣的;关心的
interesting adj. 有趣的;有意思的

examples.en: I'm interested in playing basketball.
examples.cn: 我的爱好是打篮球。

examples.en: What an interesting story!
examples.cn: 多有趣的故事啊!

examples.en: Pudong International Airport is one of the biggest airports in the world.
examples.cn: 浦东国际机场是世界上最大的机场之一。

examples.en: Please show me how to use WeChat to talk with each other on the Internet.
examples.cn: 请告诉我如何使用微信在互联网上互相交谈。

examples.en: Then you will possibly understand your questions better and get right answers on the day of the interview.
examples.cn: 这样你可能在面试那天更好地理解问题并正确回答。

translations.translation: 到...里;向内;(表示状态的变化)变成;进入

examples.en: It turned into ice.
examples.cn: 它变成了冰。

examples.en: Could you introduce us three historical events in the Tang Dynasty?
examples.cn: 你能向我们介绍唐朝的3个历史事件吗?

examples.en: Edison invented quite a lot of things during his life.
examples.cn: 爱迪生在他一生中发明了很多东西。

expand: inventor n. 发明家,创造者

examples.en: Making paper is one of the greatest inventions of ancient Chinese people.
examples.cn: 造纸是中国古代人民最伟大的发明之一。

examples.en: Internet is a great invention. It makes the world “smaller”.
examples.cn: 互联网是一项伟大的发明。它使世界变“小”了。

examples.en: The machine is named after its inventor.
examples.cn: 这台机器是以其发明者的名字命名的。

examples.en: The police investigate the cause of car accident.
examples.cn: 警方正在调查这起车祸的原因。

examples.en: We received Peter's invitation and went to his birthday party happily.
examples.cn: 我们收到了彼得的邀请,并愉快地参加他的生日聚会。

examples.en: Some of the Chinese celebrities were invited to attend the Cannes International Film Festival.
examples.cn: 一些中国名人应邀出席戛纳国际电影节。

examples.en: Iron and wood have different natures.
examples.cn: 铁和木头的性质不同。

examples.en: Taiwan is the biggest island of China. I hope to visit it soon.
examples.cn: 台湾是中国最大的岛屿。我希望不久能参观这座岛。

translations.translation: 意大利人的;意大利语的

examples.en: The Italian Prime Minister paid her first visit to China last July.
examples.cn: 去年7月意大利总理首次访华。

examples.en: I can speak Italian.
examples.cn: 我会说意大利语。

examples.en: Last summer I went to France. This year I'm going to Italy instead.
examples.cn: 去年夏天我去了法国,而今年我要去意大利。

translations.translation: 项目;节目;一件商品(物品);一则

examples.en: I think we ought to pass on to the next item.
examples.cn: 我想我们应该接着开始下一个项目。

examples.en: I'd like to buy that jacket, but the colour is not my first choice.
examples.cn: 我想买那件夹克,但颜色不是我的首选。

examples.en: I like to eat jam.
examples.cn: 我喜欢吃果酱。

examples.en: I'm sure there will be fewer traffic jams in the future.
examples.cn: 我确信未来交通堵塞的情况会越来越少。

examples.en: It happened on January the seventeenth.
examples.cn: 事情发生在1月17日。

examples.en: Thousands of lives were lost in the terrible earthquake that happened in Japan.
examples.cn: 在日本发生的可怕地震中,有成千上万的人失去了生命。

expand: Japanese adj. 日本的;日语的;日本人的

translations.translation: 日本的;日语的;日本人的

examples.en: I am fond of Japanese food. It's light and delicious.
examples.cn: 我很喜欢日本的食物。它清淡而美味。

examples.en: I am a Japanese so I can speak Japanese.
examples.cn: 我是日本人,所以我会说日语。

examples.en: I don't want to buy the jeans because neither the colour nor the size fits me.
examples.cn: 我不想买那条牛仔裤,因为颜色和尺码都不适合我。

examples.en: The local government is planning to create more jobs for young people.
examples.cn: 当地政府正计划为年轻人创造更多的就业机会。

examples.en: It must be fantastic if more students join in the charity show tomorrow.
examples.cn: 要是有更多的学生参加明天的慈善演出,那一定很棒。

examples.en: We had better treat it as a joke.
examples.cn: 我们最好把它当作玩笑。

examples.en: I like to joke.
examples.cn: 我喜欢开玩笑。

examples.en: I want to be a journalist after graduation.
examples.cn: 毕业后我想当记者。

examples.en: Do you know if they had a good journey home?
examples.cn: 你知道他们回家的旅途是否愉快?

translations.translation: 欢乐;高兴;乐趣;愉快;喜悦

examples.en: To my great joy, my lost watch was found.
examples.cn: 使我极为高兴的是,我丢失的手表找到了。

examples.en: The judge sentenced the bad egg to death.
examples.cn: 法官判这个混蛋死刑。

examples.en: Let's go to get a pizza and a glass of orange juice.
examples.cn: 我们去买一个比萨饼和一杯橙汁吧。

examples.en: We'll take our holiday sometime in July, I think.
examples.cn: 我想我们大概会在7月休假。

examples.en: He is good at long jump shot.
examples.cn: 他擅长远距离跳投。

examples.en: I arrived on a hot June morning.
examples.cn: 我是在6月的一个炎热的上午到达的。

translations.translation: 年少者;较年幼者;年资较浅者

examples.en: Many Junior Three students give up their hobbies because of their busy school work.
examples.cn: 许多初三学生放弃自己的兴趣爱好,因为他们忙于学校作业。

examples.en: Just then a friend drove up and gave me a ride.
examples.cn: 正在那时,一个朋友开车过来,让我搭了他的车。

examples.en: About one-third of the students in our class are keen on pop songs.
examples.cn: 我们班大约有三分之一的学生热衷于流行歌曲。

translations.translation: 保持;保存;继续不断;培育,饲养

examples.en: Amazing new products are developed constantly to keep customers excited.
examples.cn: 令人惊叹的新产品不断研发出来,让顾客保持兴奋。

examples.en: You are lucky enough to keep the book for a week.
examples.cn: 你够幸运,这本书你可以借一周。

examples.en: I searched every corner of the house for the key, but couldn't find it.
examples.cn: 我找遍了房子的每一个角落,却还是没找到那把钥匙。

examples.en: The keyboard is used to put information into the computer.
examples.cn: 键盘用于把信息输入电脑。

examples.en: In winter, Chinese students like to kick the Jianzi to keep themselves warm.
examples.cn: 在冬天,中国学生喜欢踢毽子取暖。

examples.en: I am kidding.
examples.cn: 我在开玩笑。

examples.en: I don't go out much, mainly because I have to look after the kids.
examples.cn: 我不太出去,主要是因为我要照顾孩子。

examples.en: Tornadoes swept across the South America last month. At least 28 people were killed.
examples.cn: 上个月龙卷风横扫南美洲,至少有28人死亡。

examples.en: Apple costs eighteen yuan a kilogram.
examples.cn: 苹果每公斤18元。

examples.en: My home is half a kilometre away from here.
examples.cn: 我家离这儿有半公里。

examples.en: Most tomatoes are red when ripe, but some kinds are yellow.
examples.cn: 大多数西红柿成熟时是红色的,但有些品种是黄色的。

examples.en: It's very kind of you to help me with my English.
examples.cn: 你真好,帮我学英语。

expand: kindness n. 仁慈;善良;好意

examples.en: Most girls in our kindergarten like to play with dolls.
examples.cn: 我们幼儿园大多数女孩子喜欢玩洋娃娃。

examples.en: Your smile is the best way to show people your kindness.
examples.cn: 你的微笑是向人们展示你善意的最好方式。

examples.en: The story goes that long ago there lived a king.
examples.cn: 传说很久以前那儿有个国王。

examples.en: Billy, is your mother cooking meat in the kitchen? It smells so nice!
examples.cn: 比利,你妈妈是不是在厨房炖肉?味道很香!

examples.en: My brother is flying a kite in the park.
examples.cn: 我的弟弟在公园里放风筝。

examples.en: The children learned to put their knives and forks down on the plates after eating.
examples.cn: 孩子们学会用完餐后,把刀叉放在盘子上。

examples.en: They heard a knock at the front door.
examples.cn: 他们听到前门有人敲门。

examples.en: Lily and Mary have known each other for seven years.
examples.cn: 莉莉和玛丽相识已有7年了。

examples.en: He has a wide knowledge of history and can answer almost any question about it.
examples.cn: 他有渊博的历史知识,几乎能回答任何有关历史的问题。

examples.en: We usually have Science in the science lab.
